# Walkthrough: Cafe Orders Feature Implementation

I have successfully implemented the full-stack Cafe Orders feature, enabling students to order food online and cafe vendors to manage their menus and orders.

## Key Accomplishments

### 1. Vendor Management System
- **Vendor Authentication**: Created a dedicated login for cafe staff at [vendor_login.html](file:///C:/Users/tusha/OneDrive/Desktop/FSD/OneCampus_VER8/frontend/login/vendor_login.html).
- **Menu Management**: In [hotel_view.html](file:///C:/Users/tusha/OneDrive/Desktop/FSD/OneCampus_VER8/frontend/cafe/hotel_view.html), vendors can now add new items (name, price, image) and delete existing ones.
- **Real-time Order Dashboard**: Vendors see incoming orders in an "Ongoing" list and can mark them as "Done", moving them to the "Completed" section.

### 2. Student Ordering Experience
- **Dynamic Menus**: [CafeM.html](file:///C:/Users/tusha/OneDrive/Desktop/FSD/OneCampus_VER8/frontend/cafe/CafeM.html) now fetches real-time menu data from the database.
- **Improved Cart**: [cart.html](file:///C:/Users/tusha/OneDrive/Desktop/FSD/OneCampus_VER8/frontend/cafe/cart.html) groups items by cafe, allows quantity adjustments, and handles the checkout process.
- **Local Persistence**: The cart state is maintained across page refreshes using `localStorage`.

### 3. Smart Redirection
- **Landing Page Integration**: Updated [nav_logic.js](file:///C:/Users/tusha/OneDrive/Desktop/FSD/OneCampus_VER8/frontend/landing/js/nav_logic.js) to automatically redirect logged-in cafe vendors to their dashboard ([hotel_view.html](file:///C:/Users/tusha/OneDrive/Desktop/FSD/OneCampus_VER8/frontend/cafe/hotel_view.html)) when they click on "Cafe Orders".

## Verification Details

### Automated Tests
- Verified backend routes:
    - `POST /api/vendor/login`
    - `GET /api/menus/:cafeName`
    - `POST /api/orders`
    - `PATCH /api/orders/:id/status`

### Manual Verification
- [x] Vendor Login -> Dashboard Access
- [x] Add/Delete Menu Items
- [x] Landing Page -> Redirect to Dashboard (for vendors)
- [x] Cafe Menu -> Add to Cart
- [x] Cart -> Place Order -> Success Redirect

## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TD
    User((Student/Vendor)) --> Landing[index.html]
    Landing -- Role: Cafe --> VD[hotel_view.html]
    Landing -- Role: Student --> CH[CafeH.html]
    CH --> CM[CafeM.html]
    CM --> CR[cart.html]
    CR -- API --> BK[Node.js Backend]
    VD -- API --> BK
    BK --> DB[(MongoDB)]
```

